	<td bgcolor="#160022" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Petel, you are right that "first contact aggro" would make my reasoning wrong if it is more than one concuss (1c) worth. As I said in one previous post, i didnt belive it so, since one draught was enough to overcome any initial aggro ..but then I noticed that it is believed that aggro from one draught is 3c, not 1c - so real test should be done with spell that is just under 1c aggro.<br />
<br />
What I'm trying to do here is to accept existence of both variables in aggro generation:<br />
<br />
1) "initial aggro" as mentioned by Istari, around ~2c, lets call it (By)<br />
2) "first contact aggro" as mentioned on warrior thread (Bi), unknow aggro (&gt; 1c if Petel notion is right)<br />
<br />
Now, both are interesting concepts, but I'm trying to be sure they are both right. <br />
<br />
You will notice that noone on warrior thread mentioned "initial aggro", but that can be ignored since existence of that aggro would not invalidate their tests - they were always adding aggro.<br />
<br />
More interesting is that Istari did not use or mention "first contact aggro", and if that aggro is Bi &gt; 1c, it would invalidate all his equations. For example, instead of starting 2c/2c (pull) , it should be 2c/3c (pull) ... would need 10 (or 8) instead of 9/7 concuss to steal aggro, etc...<br />
<br />
And if "first contact aggro" is less that 1c, then my two previous posts (about concuss pull and proximity aggro) remain, where I see inconsistency with those 2c initiall aggro and concuss pull.<br />
<br />
If i manage to get time, I will try to test if "first contact aggro" (Bi) is more or less than 1c. So far on warrior thread they say that 16 first contact aggros is less than one complete heal aggro, but its possible than 1 CH = 16c if 1 SoS=9c, so its not conclusive.<br />
<br />
But regardless of result, ie regardless if first contact aggro is more or less than 1c, I see some inconsistency with Istari theory:<br />
a) if  Bi &gt; 1c, those 2c/2c equations are not valid<br />
b) if Bi &lt; 1c, that theory still does not explain how pulling with concuss (aggro=Bi+By-1c &lt; By) will keep me more aggro than proximity aggro from other people in group (aggro=By)<br />
<br />
Btw, I'm not trying here to be negative on Istari theory, in fact i like both ideas about initial aggro and first contact aggro, but I'm just trying to be sure both are valid.<br />
</font></p>
	
