	<a name="post275928"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Nenad</b></font><br>
	
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Apprentice</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>






	
	<td bgcolor="29003E" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >I decided to do some actual tests to hopefully find out which one is true. <br />
<br />
What tests try to find out?<br />
-----------------------------------<br />
<br />
1) does "first contact aggro" (Bi) exists and how big it is? Theory so far by war board is that this Bi exists, its small, and Bi <br />
<br />
gets only person who first aggro mob. <br />
<br />
2) does "initial aggro" (Ba) exists and how big it is? Theory so far by Istari is that it exists and is about 2 concuss (2c or ~800) <br />
<br />
big, and everyone gets it as soon as they aggro mob<br />
<br />
3) is casting concussion before first nuke useful? (this should be answered as soon as question 2 is answered)<br />
<br />
4) how big is "+1" addition on warrior taunt (Ti)? (since warrior was helping me do tests , this was easy to test also :)<br />
<br />
5) can we go into "negative" hate?<br />
<br />
<br />
Some background on hate theories so far, as I understood:<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
<br />
TotalHate = Hate + HateBonus<br />
<br />
Aggro = TotalHate * Modifier<br />
<br />
Hate is what you get using weapons, spells or taunt, and what gets lowered by concuss.<br />
HateBonus is already mentioned "first contact aggro" Bi, sitting aggro, distance aggro etc. It is possible that distance aggro is not <br />
<br />
part of hate bonus but it is part of Modifier, but its irelevant here.<br />
<br />
<br />
According to <a href="http://www.thesteelwarrior.org/forum/showthread.php?postid=32130#post32130" target="_blank">SteelWarrior board theory</a>, if you <br />
<br />
pull mob without some damage, you get :<br />
Puller_Total_Hate = 0 + Bi<br />
<br />
where Bi is "first contact aggro" that initial puller gets, while for example warrior waiting in your group at that moment, even if <br />
<br />
he gets at hate list due to being close to pulled mob,  have:<br />
War_Total_Hate= 0 + 0<br />
<br />
If war use Taunt, each successful taunt will make his "Hate" equals largest current  "Hate" plus some small addition "+1" or Ti. So <br />
<br />
if some puller pulled and got above hate, and warrior taunt, he will get:<br />
War_Total_Hate = (0+Ti) + 0<br />
<br />
Important is to notice that HateBonus is not used in taunt. And since Ti is smaller than Bi, in such situations warrior will NOT get <br />
<br />
aggro from puller after first successful taunt. Tests on war boars shows that he would need 4 taunts to do that, so Ti=Bi/4. There is <br />
<br />
no estimate on how big Bi or Ti is, only that aggro from 63Ti+Bi &lt; aggro from one CH<br />
<br />
According to <a href="http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&threadid=8643&highlight=concussion" target="_blank">Ishtari theory</a> , everyone <br />
<br />
starts not with zero but with some predefined initial hate after they first time gets to hate list. Lets call that "initial aggro" <br />
<br />
Ba. As I mentioned, current theory says that Ba ~ 2c. So in previous example where puller pull mob to camp, where war wait, we would <br />
<br />
have:<br />
Puller_Total_Aggro= Ba + Bi<br />
War_Total_Aggro= Ba + 0<br />
<br />
Notice that  on warrior board theory, they didnt use Ba anywhere, while in Istari teory there is no Bi anywhere. That is also one <br />
<br />
reason why i wanted to do this tests.<br />
<br />
Test setup:<br />
---------------------------<br />
I wanted to have greater accuracy for tests than previous "close to 1c" tests, ie what I'm trying to test is possibly smaller than <br />
<br />
aggro from 1 concussion (1c ~ 400), so I needed more precise testing method than usual " I will cast nuke, then cast concuss till i <br />
<br />
lose aggro", since such tests have accuracy of only +/- 1c. So I decided to use wiz nuke small enough to give at least 1/10th concuss <br />
<br />
accuracy, or more precisely, to generate less than 40 aggro. I decided on lvl 4 wiz fire based spell "Shock of Fire" (~16 damage)<br />
<br />
Test group consisted of one wizard (me:) and one warrior (uros who never stopped whining how "this tests are stupid" :)<br />
<br />
Wizard used:<br />
 - for pulls, getting close to kos mobs or pathetic melee attack (both to see if there is difference, there was not)<br />
 - for nukes lvl 4 wiz fire based spell "Shock of Fire"<br />
 - for concuss EP pants and normal concuss (both to see if there is difference, there was not)<br />
<br />
Warrior used:<br />
 - for pulls, getting close to kos mobs or fist melee attack ~20ish damage (both to see if there is difference, there was not)<br />
 - for damage - nothing<br />
 - for taunt - taunt :)<br />
<br />
Mobs:<br />
 - solB kobolds (mostly)<br />
 - solB bats<br />
<br />
In all tests, after puller pulled, both wiz and tank were positioned at same distance from mob, to eliminate proximity aggro. <br />
Also none used damage or any other shields. <br />
Tank was standing sidewise so not to use riposte or any other automatic discipline.<br />
In other word, after warrior initially pulled, he was not generating new aggro while mob was hitting him.<br />
All tests were repeated at least several times, and that should be conclusive enough since no test relied on low margins of <br />
<br />
difference.<br />
<br />
<br />
Test intentions:<br />
 - T1: find how much aggro/hate is "Shock of Fire"<br />
 - T2: find how much aggro/hate is "first contact aggro" Bi?<br />
 - T3: find how much aggro/hate is "initial aggro" Ba?<br />
 - T4: check how much aggro/hate is "taunt addition" Ti compared to Bi?<br />
 - T5: one way to check if we can go into negative hate<br />
<br />
<br />
Test T1: find how much aggro/hate is "Shock of Fire"<br />
-----------------------------------------------<br />
1) WAR pulls mob<br />
2) WIZ use some middle sized nuke to gain for sure more than one conc aggro<br />
3) WAR use taunt untill gets aggro<br />
4) WIZ use "Shock" untill gets aggro (so now WIZ aggro = WAr aggro, +/- one "Shock" aggro)<br />
5) WIZ use "concuss" to lose aggro<br />
6) WIZ start using "Shock" and count untill regain aggro<br />
<br />
Result: it took 25-29 "Shocks" to cover aggro range of one concuss, so we can say that "Shock" aggro was around 1/27th of 1c, which <br />
<br />
totaly satisfy my intention to have at least 1/10th precision. Numerically that would be about 15 aggro for one "Shock"<br />
<br />
<br />
Test T2: find how much aggro/hate is "first contact aggro" Bi?<br />
-----------------------------------------------<br />
1) WAR pulls mob. he now gets WarHate=Ba+Bi. Wiz start Hate= Ba<br />
2) WIZ start using "Shock" and count untill gets aggro<br />
<br />
Result: it took 6-8 "Shocks" to overcome initial aggro difference, Bi. This shows that Bi really exists, and puts its numerical value <br />
<br />
at around 100 aggro.<br />
<br />
Test T3: find how much aggro/hate is "initial aggro" Ba?<br />
--------------------------------------------------------<br />
1) WAR pulls mob, his WarHate= Ba+Bi, WizHate= Ba<br />
2) WIZ cast concuss on mob 10 times. WizHate now = 0<br />
3) WIZ start using "Shock" and count untill gets aggro<br />
<br />
Result: it took 7-8 "Shocks" to overcome aggro difference, which in this case is Ba+Bi. So we have Ba+Bi~7, and in test T2 we have <br />
<br />
Bi~7, which means that Ba~0 !  In other words, there is NONE difference in this case in how many "Shocks" i neeed to cast to get <br />
<br />
aggro from war puller, regardles if i use concuss before my first nuke or not. <br />
<br />
<br />
Test T4: check how much aggro/hate is "taunt addition" Ti compared to Bi?<br />
--------------------------------------------------------<br />
1) WIZ pulls mob, his WizHate= Bi, WarHate= 0<br />
3) WAR use Taunt untill gets aggro, and count succesful taunts needed<br />
<br />
Result: WAR needed always 4 succesful taunts, so it confirm test done on war board that Ti=Bi/4. Since we now know that Bi~100, that <br />
<br />
makes Ti~25. Also we tried this test with war pulling, wiz getting equal aggro and then war using taunt, and WAR always needed only <br />
<br />
one successful taunt, which further confirm that theory (since in that case wiz had Bi in HateBonus)<br />
<br />
<br />
Test T5: one way to check if we can go into negative hate<br />
-----------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
1) WIZ pulls, and then concuss, WizHate= ( 0 or -1c ) + Bi <br />
2) WAR use Taunt untill gets aggro, and count succesful taunts needed<br />
<br />
Result: WAR needed always 4 succesful taunts, which is same result as T4, and shows that concussion can not lower Bi, which is as <br />
<br />
expected since Bi goes into HateBonus, while concuss lower Hate part. this further proves that Hate part of TotalHate CAN NOT go <br />
<br />
negative.<br />
<br />
<br />
Answers to initial questions:<br />
----------------------------------<br />
1) Q: does "first contact aggro" (Bi) exists and how big it is? Theory so far by war board is that this Bi exists, its small, and Bi <br />
<br />
gets only person who first aggro mob. <br />
   A: Yes, it does exists, and it is about 100 aggro  , as shown in T2<br />
<br />
2) Q: does "initial aggro" (Ba) exists and how big it is? Theory so far by Istari is that it exists and is about 2 concuss (2c or <br />
<br />
~800) big, and everyone gets it as soon as they aggro mob<br />
   A: No, it does not exists, as shown in T3 and T2<br />
<br />
3) Q: is casting concussion before first nuke useful? <br />
   A: No, it appears is not useful, it follow from answer 2.<br />
<br />
4) Q: how big is "+1" addition on warrior taunt (Ti)? <br />
   A: Ti is Bi/4 ~ 25 aggro, as shown in T4<br />
<br />
5) Q: can we go into "negative" hate?<br />
   A: No, there is no "negative hate", as shown in T5 and also T3 (10 concuss used)<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >__________________<br>
