	<td bgcolor="29003E" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >quote:</font><hr><i>Originally posted by Istari </i><br />
"Negative Aggro" = FALSE<br />
"Limited to Positive Aggro" = TRUE<br />
<br />
It is assertable that there is no negative aggro, since it does not equate with the system. however, in a system where aggro is always at least 0, the representation of the system is in harmony with its reality. there is no negative aggro. [/B]<hr></blockquote> <br />
<br />
This in an of itself is a hypothysis. You may think you have solved the puzzle but you have not.<br />
<br />
What you concluded was<br />
Casting SoS then 9 concussions would get mob to turn away.<br />
Casting 20 concussions then SoS and then 7 concussions would get mob to turn away.<br />
<br />
Theoretically this would state that no mater the # of concussions you cast before, solong as its more than 2, you cannot reduce your agro more than -800 from base.<br />
<br />
From this we can theorize still yet 2 possibilities:<br />
1: You start off with 0 points on the agro list and can never drop below -800. <br />
2: You start off with 800 points on the agro list and can never drop below 0.<br />
<br />
Both of these would support the original statement.<br />
<br />
However the original question was, Can you have negative agro. Theoretically yes. But this will never be answered fully unless we are able to look at the code.<br />
Having negative agro does not mean that you do not have agro. It would just mean that you are one of the lowest on the agro list.<br />
<br />
Casting concussion to pull would lower your initial agro to -400 of normal whatever normal is. But as you are the only one on the list you will be attacked.</font></p>
	
