	<td bgcolor="29003E" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Ok, I can provide some insight perhaps from an old Rogues point of view.<br />
<br />
Back when Evade dropped you to the bottom of the hate-list you could do some interesting things.  The easiest example of this was pulling a mob into camp where noone was doing anything.  Evade and it goes for the next person.  Not a shock there... conclusion: prox-secondary has a value of at least 1 and likely more (as if I were dropped to zero I could have run away if I were oor, and that was not possible).<br />
<br />
Another point on that... one could drag an aggro mob (prox-aggroed say) through othere people and then evade a vast distance away and it would switch out and chase those people, who had done nothing but at some point be close to the target.  Conclusion: you get added to the hate list in some manner if you are inside the magic radius.<br />
<br />
Evading a targetted mob prior to it even getting near to me (ie no prox aggro even yet) gave the usual message but made *no* discernable differance once the mob hit camp.  Back then I would always aggro if I backstabbed at first opportunity and I would still do so if I pre-evaded.  No combonation of evading even after contact would change this, there was a need to build some tank-hate.  Oddly, one could atack and then evade and provide a decent buffer of hate for the tank, although that was likely a time buffer more than anything.<br />
<br />
After Evade was fixed to be a set drop in hate or a drop to below the second most hated, things were different but much the same.  In the vast majority of situations, evade now functions like (presumably) concussion does.  In this paradigm, evading before gaining any aggro is a complete waste.  If you want to lay low you might as well just stay oor and do nothing.  That or hit a baby nuke and conc afterwards.<br />
<br />
In my opinion you cannot get to "negative hate" and any efforts to do so are wasted.  You *can* drop off the prox-hate to a minimum but I've never seen any behavior that would suggest this is more than perhaps 10 hate tops.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >__________________<br>
Maurader<br />
The Nameless</font></p></p>
	<p></p>
