<table bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#663399"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#160022" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post276535"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Nenad</b></font><br>
	
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Apprentice</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>






	
	<td bgcolor="#160022" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Original question here was not "can you have negative aggro" but "Is there any point in concussioning prior to landing the first DD?"<br />
<br />
So, it is irelevant if everyone start at 800 and can go to 0, or everyone start at 0 and can go to -800. In both those cases, it would be useful to cast 2 concus before nuke.<br />
<br />
Real question here was: is there really such 800 buffer?<br />
<br />
I think that my tests, among other things, indicate that  there is no such buffer. It is interesting that Istari's tests show existence of such buffer. Short of repeating his tests, I have no idea why there is difference in those test results, unless it was because they used less precise measurement method (ie +/- one concuss) while I used 1/27th of one concuss<br />
<br />
Anyway, from my tests follows my conclusion, or answer to original question:  <br />
<br />
There is NO point in concussioning prior to landing the first DD.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >__________________<br>
